      <item>
        <title>Mobile Error // Unhandled Promise Rejection - can&#39;t read the WP REST API</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[David]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>It seems to be a problem with the implementation we did to deprecate the <code>URL</code> constructor that we exported from <code>frontity</code>:</p>
<aside class="onebox githubblob">
  <header class="source">
      <a href="https://github.com/frontity/frontity/blob/2bdf7dbe44fec3b0c08aae7175bee76d47811a41/packages/frontity/src/utils/url.ts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com</a>
  </header>
  <article class="onebox-body">
    <h4><a href="https://github.com/frontity/frontity/blob/2bdf7dbe44fec3b0c08aae7175bee76d47811a41/packages/frontity/src/utils/url.ts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">frontity/frontity/blob/2bdf7dbe44fec3b0c08aae7175bee76d47811a41/packages/frontity/src/utils/url.ts</a></h4>
<pre><code class="lang-ts">/**
 * DEPRECATED.
 *
 * To be removed in the v2 version. Now that we've deprecated Node 8,
 * maintaining this is no longer required.
 *
 * It was meant to be used for compatibility with Node 8, where the global
 * `URL` was not present and therefore this was not possible without importing
 * URL from `"url"`.
 *
 * @example
 * ```js
 * const url = new URL("https://domain.com");
 * ```
 */

import { warn } from "@frontity/error";

/**
 * Re-export to add a deprecation warning.
</code></pre>

  This file has been truncated. <a href="https://github.com/frontity/frontity/blob/2bdf7dbe44fec3b0c08aae7175bee76d47811a41/packages/frontity/src/utils/url.ts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">show original</a>

  </article>
  <div class="onebox-metadata">
    
    
  </div>
  <div style="clear: both"></div>
</aside>

<p>For some reason, it doesn’t work well in Safari (tested in version 13.1.2) and it throws an error, making the code to fail in the <a href="https://github.com/frontity/frontity/blob/45018011ca943479975b738019380a9b8203b6b0/packages/wp-source/src/actions.ts#L117-L121">init()</a> action of <code>@frontity/wp-source</code> and showing the error you mentioned.</p>
<p>I opened an issue in order to fix this (<a href="https://github.com/frontity/frontity/issues/565">frontity/frontity#565</a>). In the meantime, it should work fine using the previous version of <code>frontity</code> (1.10.1).</p>
<p>We’ll keep you posted!</p>
<hr>
<p>EDIT: We already find a solution and we are going to publish a new version today! You can wait for the new version of <code>frontity</code> instead of installing the previous one <img src="https://community.frontity.org/images/emoji/apple/blush.png?v=9" title=":blush:" class="emoji" alt=":blush:"></p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/mobile-error-unhandled-promise-rejection-cant-read-the-wp-rest-api/2830/17">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
